sections.doc_:
The `amp-list` content is provided by a JSON CORS endpoint, which is defined by the `src` attribute. The URL's protocol must be HTTPS. The response must be a JSON object containing an array property `items`, for example:
[sourcecode:json]
{
  "items": [
    {
      "title": "amp-carousel",
      "url": "https://ampbyexample.com/components/amp-carousel"
    },
    ...
  ]
}
[/sourcecode]
The list content is rendered via an [amp-mustache template](/amp-dev/documentation/components/reference/amp-mustache-v0.2.md). The template can be specified either by id, or by using a nested element. For performance reasons, we're adding `binding="no"` as we're not using `amp-bind`.

